Source: osc++
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Dimitry Ishenko <dimitry.ishenko@gmail.com>
Build-Depends:
 debhelper-compat (= 13),
 cmake (>= 3.16),
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/dimitry-ishenko-cpp/osc
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/dimitry-ishenko-cpp/osc
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/dimitry-ishenko-cpp/osc.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: libosc++
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
Description: osc++ – an OSC Library for C++
 The osc++ library allows one to easily create and parse OSC (Open Sound
 Control) packets. Ref: http://opensoundcontrol.org/
 .
 OSC is an open, transport-independent, message-based protocol developed for
 communication between computers and other multimedia devices.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libosc++-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 libosc++ (= ${binary:Version}),
Description: osc++ – an OSC Library for C++
 The osc++ library allows one to easily create and parse OSC (Open Sound
 Control) packets. Ref: http://opensoundcontrol.org/
 .
 OSC is an open, transport-independent, message-based protocol developed for
 communication between computers and other multimedia devices.
 .
 This package contains development files.
